    "tag": "KWZ",
    "text": "This is the last picture of my class done before the war in June '39. I am here in the middle behind the boss. He is Director of the college. And here is the Chief of Education of our class, who, after many years later, introduced me to my wife here in Johannesburg, in South Africa. And then, well, let's turn the page. And we got here myself in the army uniform just after the war in the occupation zone of Germany when I was working in the prosecution, interrogating the war criminals. OK. Now, now, we got here-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] these are my grandchildren-- my son, his wife, and my grandchildren in Poland, in Krakow. In the middle is my granddaughter Barbara, student of law at the university in the third year. The boy is Mark, making [INAUDIBLE] this year. And the youngest one is Marta. And now I want to show you my [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] lovely step-daughter Danuta, with her husband, a doctor of medicine, Maryk Rozwadowski, living in Canada, in Victoria, on the Vancouver Island with their three daughters. The oldest one here, you got Eva. Close to the mother is Wanda, a big sportsman. And then you got Yolanta. And at the bottom, the boy Dominik, to whom I sent geckos from South Africa when they are dry, and he enjoy it.",
